<h2>Minnesota Incentives & Rebates</h2>
<p>Minnesota offers comprehensive incentive programs that significantly reduce the cost of solar and HVAC installations. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit for solar installations through 2032, stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. This credit applies to the total system cost including equipment, installation, and permitting fees, making it one of the most valuable solar incentives available.</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Federal 30% Solar Tax Credit:</strong> Available for residential and commercial solar installations, covering panels, inverters, mounting equipment, and installation costs. The credit can be carried forward to future tax years if it exceeds current tax liability, and there's no maximum limit on the credit amount.</li>
<li><strong>Solar Rewards Program:</strong> Xcel Energy's Solar Rewards program offers upfront incentives for solar installations, currently providing \$0.06 per watt for residential systems and \$0.04 per watt for commercial systems. This program has capacity limits and operates on a first-come, first-served basis.</li>
<li><strong>Xcel Energy Rebates:</strong> The utility provides substantial rebates for high-efficiency HVAC equipment, including up to \$1,700 for ENERGY STAR certified heat pumps, \$1,200 for high-efficiency central air conditioners, and \$600 for qualifying furnaces with ECM motors.</li>
<li><strong>Made in Minnesota Solar Incentive:</strong> Additional state incentive providing \$0.05-0.18 per watt for solar systems using Minnesota-manufactured equipment, supporting local manufacturing while reducing installation costs.</li>
<li><strong>Property Tax Exemption:</strong> Solar energy systems are exempt from property tax assessments in Minnesota, ensuring that adding solar panels won't increase annual property taxes despite increasing home value.</li>
</ul>

